---
title: "Turn Noise into Actionable Insight to Answer Your Questions"
date: 2018-08-20T22:48:25.000Z
authors: ["Hakan Isik"]
link: "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=e505a529db84230467a72926ca9619ec"
---
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Answers make the world go around</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">We all have our questions; questions that we need to answer to decide the next thing, either in our personal or professional lives.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">They can be as simple and mundane as those ones: How are you? Coffee or tea? Will it rain today? Lunch? What should I wear for the meeting? How will traffic be today? Etc.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Or as complex and multi-dimensional as those: Are we progressing according to our original plan? Will stock prices go back up? How can I reduce my costs? Why is internet banking down? Etc.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">In any case, <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">we need the right data in the right context</span> to able to answer our questions and take the next step.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">The situation is not different for companies</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; ffont-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Well, it is actually much more difficult for them considering ever increasing user expectations, market pressure, amount of data and technological complexity.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Because now, they need to find the answers to their questions and act accordingly faster than ever in order to connect their business with their employees, partners, customers, and keep them happy.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Luckily, so far most of the enterprises have come to the realization that they have a secret best friend who is willing to help them with those challenges: Their IT.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">They knew that there was no way for them to achieve <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">visibility and agility</span> they need, without the support of their IT and accepted the fact that &#34;IT is business and business is IT&#34;.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; ffont-size: 11.0pt;"><img src="d144eda1db84230467a72926ca96198d.iix" /></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">IT knew it all along but had its own challenges</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">On the other hand, IT always knew that data was the essential ingredient for the required visibility and agility.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">That&#39;s why IT kept collecting not only technical but also business events, metrics, logs, etc. coming from all those different sources with different shapes.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And they also tried to;</p>
<ul><li>Put all that data in a <span style="font-size: 11.0pt; color: #6fb8a0;">business-relevant</span><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;"> context</span></li><li>Make it <span style="font-size: 11.0pt; color: #6fb8a0;">accessible</span><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;"> by all required parties</span></li><li>Automate<span style="font-size: 11.0pt;"> the analysis process so that they could answer their questions as fast as possible.</span></li></ul>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;"><img src="3e542125db84230467a72926ca96197f.iix" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;"> </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Of course that was easier said than done!</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">First of all, getting the data from various sources, normalizing it and putting it into a single source of truth wasn’t an easy job in traditional <span style="color: #c00000;">silo-based environments</span>.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">There were <span style="color: #c00000;">lots of integrations</span> to maintain and lots <span style="color: #c00000;">departmental silos</span> to bring together which required lots of time and effort.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">On top of that, IT had <span style="color: #c00000;">limited analytical and machine learning capabilities</span> which made things even more difficult in terms of automating key processes such as Root Cause Analysis.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">As a result, IT got stuck in a <span style="color: #c00000;">reactive fire-fighting mode</span> where even answering a basic question like &#34;Why are users experiencing slowness in our application?&#34; is a significant challenge.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">BTW, seriously, what is the root cause of that slowness? </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Now, among many other things, that is something ServiceNow can help you with.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">But before getting into &#34;How&#34; part, there is one thing I want to emphasize: <span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;">The Now Platform!</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">The Now Platform allows us to <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">eliminate silos by bring together processes, systems, people, and data across the enterprise within a single data model and without requiring internal integrations</span>.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And the capabilities I&#39;m about to talk about are nothing but platform features which can be used with the single data model and with any application created either by ServiceNow or by users on the Now Platform.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Just fix the problem already!</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">OK! We need two things to solve the issue and keep our users happy:</p>
<ol><li>Right level of visibility, to know what is going on within my business and whether my users are happy or not.</li><li>Agility, to act fast enough to solve problems before they negatively impact my users and my business, and prevent them wherever possible.</li></ol>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Let&#39;s see how ServiceNow can help us  with those two:</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#1: Business-aware discovery:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Let&#39;s start with real time visibility.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Driving real time visibility starts with understanding our operational landscape.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Once we have a clear view of our business processes, supporting business services and underlying applications and infrastructure, we can accurately answer questions in many different domains such as Root Cause Analysis, Incident Management, Change Management, Asset Management, SecOps, etc.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">There are many potential sources available to help us identify and map our environment; and using those sources, the Now Platform gives us the ability to both discover and map our services in context with the business.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">The ultimate goal is to bring all of these sources together to provide the most accurate, real time view of our business services.  We call this our business aware data layer.  This layer allows operational decisions to be made in context to business services.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="49f64e29db88630467a72926ca9619c3.iix" /></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#2: Event collection &amp; management:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Since now we have a clear view of our business, it is time to bring that view to life.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">For this, we need data!</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">ServiceNow allows us to ingest data in forms of events from multiple monitoring sources up and down the stack to bring together a unified view of health in context to your business services.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">This helps us to fill in the visibility gaps protecting our current investments.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">It also provides event management capabilities which helps us to identify health issues across the datacenter on a single management console allowing us to focus on what matters for our business.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="a77a02a9db0c630467a72926ca961972.iix" /></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#3: Alert correlation:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">One of the most important of those event management capabilities is &#34;Automated Alert Correlation&#34;.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">The first thing ServiceNow does when it gets technical events, is turning them into meaningful, business-relevant alerts.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">That not only reduces the number of things that we need to keep an eye on significantly, but also shows us the right things to focus on.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And then using machine learning techniques, it starts learning patterns in those alerts in order to automatically create alert groups highlighting cause-consequence couples as primary and secondary alerts.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Now, instead of dealing with thousands of technical events, we&#39;re looking at only a bunch of alerts giving us meaningful hints regarding potential root causes of the issues we&#39;re having.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"> <img src="0b9fc6a5dbcc630467a72926ca96190d.iix" /></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#4: Anomaly detection:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">But, events aren&#39;t the only data type we can leverage to achieve complete visibility.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Metrics, can also give us great insight about trends of our KPIs and root causes of our problems.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And ServiceNow allows us to ingest raw metrics from various monitoring sources too.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">The main issues with them, though, as they behave differently from system to system, application to application, architecture to architecture, enterprise to enterprise; if we try to handle them using traditional methods like static thresholds, they can potentially create lots of noise in forms of false alarms.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">At this point, again machine learning capabilities come to rescue us.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="27f01ea5db00a30467a72926ca961952.iix" /></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;" colspan="3">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">The platform automatically learns from historical metric data, and builds standard statistical models to project expected metric values along with upper and lower bounds.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">It then uses these projections to detect statistical outliers and to calculate anomaly scores indicating anomalous behavior of CIs which may not be captured by events.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">As a result of that process, we get anomaly alerts which can be promoted to regular alerts and this helps us to get rid of false alerts while only capturing the real ones.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And those regular alerts also contributes to alert correlation mechanism as any other alerts to enhance our visibility.</p>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#5: Alert-CI binding:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Then Event Management uses event rules and other mechanisms to automatically bind alerts to CI information from the CMDB.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">This simplifies and speeds up diagnosis and remediation processes revealing impacted CIs within business service context.</p>

<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt; color: #6fb8a0;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">#6: Collaboration of processes</span>:</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Yes, our main goal is trying to figure out why we&#39;re having slow transactions in our application; but before moving forward with that, I&#39;d like to take a quick detour into a bigger picture.<br /> Our business consists of multiple moving parts and those parts run on various tightly coupled processes.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="c2741e29db80a30467a72926ca961923.iix" /></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;" colspan="3">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">As we&#39;re looking for answers within our business, most of the time we need to move back and forward between those processes using overlapping subsets of our whole data.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Let&#39;s take our case as an example:</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">We&#39;re trying to answer one very simple question; &#34;Why are users experiencing slowness in our application?&#34;</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">While doing that, there are multiple dimensions that we have to take into account:</p>
<ul style="margin-left: .375in; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in;" type="disc"><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Which CIs have contributed to it and what are their relations?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Have we already created an incident and assigned it to the right people/group?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Has any of the recently performed changes caused the slowness?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">It that something we&#39;ve seen before? Should we treat it as a problem?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Do we already have a solution to it in our knowledge base?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">How are we doing with our SLAs?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Do we need to be concerned from a security standpoint?</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">What is its impact to out business?</span></li></ul>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Interesting enough, even though all those questions somewhat look independent from each other, because they&#39;re using highly correlated datasets, they significantly contribute to each others answers.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Considering the collaboration between various processes, it doesn’t really make sense to think or position them separately.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And that&#39;s the point where <span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;">The Now Platform</span> steps in and provides its biggest value.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">It allows us to <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">eliminate silos by bring together processes, systems, people, and data across the enterprise within a single data model and without requiring internal integrations</span>.</p>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#7: Root cause analysis:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">At this point, we have a good view of our business services and they&#39;re clearly reflecting their current state in real time.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">We&#39;re actually in a good position to diagnose the issue.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">But ServiceNow provides us one more machine learning capability in order to fully automate the root cause analysis process for achieving the desired agility.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="61b71aaddbc0a30467a72926ca9619b2.iix" /> </td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;" colspan="3">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Event Management applies root cause analysis algorithms to identify root cause CIs within the impacted services and allows users to drill down and pinpoint which CIs and alerts are affecting business service and application health.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">This information helps us to dramatically reduce Mean Time To Repair and move to a more proactive state from our current reactive state.</p>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#8: Predictive alerts:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">ServiceNow can take this even further.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Remember, event management gives us the ability to group alerts capturing patterns in our alert flow.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">It can also highlight the causal alerts and associate related ones to it.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="99f85ae5db04a30467a72926ca9619c8.iix" /></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;" colspan="3">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">As an extension of this machine learning capability, when ServiceNow event management captures a pattern that it has seen before, as it knows potential consequences it creates a predictive alert to give us heads up.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">This is invaluable as it gives us the ability to go beyond being proactive preventing issues before they even happen.</p>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<table style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 12.0pt;"><strong><span style="color: #6fb8a0;">#9: Automated remediation:</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Once we determine root cause of events either with real-time or predictive capabilities, it is critical that we remediate them as fast as possible.</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">The Now Platform helps us to close the loop providing automation capabilities to drive remediation related actions.</p>
</td><td style="vertical-align: top;">  </td><td style="vertical-align: top;"><img src="dc5a1621db44a30467a72926ca9619a9.iix" /></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align: top;" colspan="3">
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Those actions can be in forms of:</p>
<ul style="margin-left: .375in; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in;" type="disc"><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Attaching a knowledge article</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Recommending a potential solution</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Creating a change request</span></li><li style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; vertical-align: middle;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt;">Triggering an automated workflow</span></li></ul>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">Regardless of whether remediation is manual or automated, the goal is resolving issues before impacting users and continuously improving the knowledge base to help drive more insightful recommendations for future cases.</p>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 14.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Healthy services, happy users</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">In summary, ServiceNow can help us to <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">reduce Mean Time To Repair </span>and <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">increase Mean Time Between Failures</span> by automating those basic operational steps:</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; margin-left: .375in; font-size: 11.0pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span>DETECT <span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> PRIORITIZE<span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;"> &gt;&gt;&gt;</span> ASSIGN <span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> DIAGNOSE<span style="font-weight: bold; color: #6fb8a0;"> &gt;&gt;&gt;</span> RESOLVE</p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;"> </p>
<p style="margin: 0in; font-size: 11.0pt;">And this ultimately leads us to <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">better quality services</span> and to <span style="color: #6fb8a0;">happy users</span>.</p>
